This document lists the third-party components used by the
Phantom-WG Frontmatter project and their respective licenses.

Phantom-WG Frontmatter has no direct Python dependencies at this
time — it relies only on the Python standard library. A runtime
binary (wstunnel) and standard OS packages are documented below.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Python Dependencies
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (none)

The Phantom-WG Frontmatter Python package uses only modules from
the Python 3.11+ standard library (argparse, json, logging,
pathlib, subprocess, ipaddress, secrets, dataclasses, etc.).

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Bundled Binaries
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

wstunnel (BSD 3-Clause License)
  Version:   10.5.2
  Upstream:  https://github.com/erebe/wstunnel
  Fork:      https://github.com/ARAS-Workspace/wstunnel
  Purpose:   WebSocket/TLS tunnel server used for Ghost Mode
             clients — wraps WireGuard UDP traffic inside a
             WebSocket over TLS to traverse networks that block
             or filter UDP.
  License:   BSD-3-Clause
  Notes:     Linux/amd64 and linux/arm64 builds ship inside this
             package as
             phantom_frontmatter/bin/lib/wstunnel_<version>_linux_<arch>.tar.gz
             and are extracted at `setup init` time. Frontmatter
             never reaches out to GitHub at runtime.
             The bundled tarballs are produced by the
             "Release Linux" workflow on the ARAS-Workspace fork.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  System Dependencies (installed via apt)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  - python3         (PSF License)
  - python3-venv    (PSF License)
  - python3-pip     (MIT)
  - socat           (GPL-2.0)
  - openssl         (Apache-2.0)
  - ca-certificates (MPL-2.0)

These are standard Debian/Ubuntu packages and are governed by
their respective licenses as distributed by the OS vendor.

socat is the data-path workhorse for the egress module: it
listens on 127.0.0.1:51820/udp and forwards every datagram to the
backend address rendered into the egress systemd unit. socat was
chosen instead of an in-house Python relay because it is a
30-year-old, single-binary, well-audited tool with no equivalent
in the Python standard library.

